## Red Wine Dataset — Complete EDA

---

## About the Dataset

```
Source  : UCI Machine Learning Repository
Rows    : 1599 wines
Columns : 12
Target  : quality (score 0-10)
```

### Features
```
Fixed Acidity        → tartaric acid content
Volatile Acidity     → acetic acid (too high = bad taste)
Citric Acid          → freshness
Residual Sugar       → sugar after fermentation
Chlorides            → salt content
Free Sulfur Dioxide  → prevents microbial growth
Total Sulfur Dioxide → total SO2
Density              → depends on alcohol & sugar
pH                   → acidity level (0-14)
Sulphates            → wine preservative
Alcohol              → % alcohol content
Quality              → target (3 to 8)
```

---

## Step 1 — Load Dataset

```python
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns

# Load directly from URL
url = "https://archive.ics.uci.edu/ml/machine-learning-databases/wine-quality/winequality-red.csv"
df = pd.read_csv(url, sep=';')

print(df.shape)        # (1599, 12)
print(df.head())
print(df.columns.tolist())
```

---

## Step 2 — Basic Info

```python
# Data types and null check
df.info()

# Statistical summary
df.describe()

# Check missing values
print(df.isnull().sum())
# Red wine dataset has NO missing values ✅

# Check duplicates
print(df.duplicated().sum())  # 240 duplicates!
df = df.drop_duplicates()
print(df.shape)  # (1359, 12)
```

---

## Step 3 — Target Variable Analysis

```python
# Quality distribution
print(df['quality'].value_counts())
# 5    681
# 6    638
# 7    199
# 4     53
# 8     18
# 3    10

plt.figure(figsize=(8,4))
sns.countplot(x='quality', data=df, palette='Reds')
plt.title("Wine Quality Distribution")
plt.show()
```

Output insight:
```
Most wines are quality 5 or 6
Very few are 3 (bad) or 8 (excellent)
→ Imbalanced dataset!
```

---

## Step 4 — Binary Classification (Good vs Bad)

```python
# Simplify: quality >= 7 → Good(1), else Bad(0)
df['quality_label'] = (df['quality'] >= 7).astype(int)

print(df['quality_label'].value_counts())
# 0 (Bad)  → 1382
# 1 (Good) →  217
# Very imbalanced → may need SMOTE!
```

