## Step 9 — Skewness Check

```python
skewness = df.skew().sort_values(ascending=False)
print(skewness)

# residual sugar      → 4.5  🚨 highly skewed
# chlorides           → 5.6  🚨 highly skewed
# free sulfur dioxide → 1.2  ⚠️  moderate
# alcohol             → 0.8  ✅  mild
```

Fix skewness:
```python
import numpy as np

df['residual sugar_log'] = np.log1p(df['residual sugar'])
df['chlorides_log']      = np.log1p(df['chlorides'])
```

